    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-11-17T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-11-17T02:00:00-05:00" n="391"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d391">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">874.00/11–1745: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative in Bulgaria</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Barnes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sofia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-11-17T09:00:00+02:00"
                            >November 17, 1945—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 18—6:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>690. As anticipated, Government has decided to go ahead with elections tomorrow.
                    Prime Minister left again for provinces yesterday evening and Minister Foreign
                    Affairs telephoned to say some time today a reply will be made to note
                    communicating contents Deptel 373.</p>
                <p>Reaction official circles is that US Government never goes much farther than
                    merely to communicate notes; therefore, the contents thereof need not be taken
                    too seriously. In this connection, I have come to believe that course
                    recommended with respect to General Stoichev by Regent Ganev has much merit.
                    (Remytel 686 November 15). Such action would at least dot a few “i’s” and cross
                    a few <pb facs="0397" n="385" xml:id="pg_385"/> “t’s” here, and at same time US
                    Government would be sacrificing nothing.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Moscow as No. 314.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Barnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
